==Rules of classical predicate calculus==

In the following rules, formula_67 is exactly like formula_2 except for having the term formula_69 wherever formula_2 has the free variable formula_71.

;Universal Generalization (or Universal Introduction):
: formula_72
: formula_73

Restriction 1: formula_69 is a variable which does not occur in formula_2.

Restriction 2: formula_69 is not mentioned in any hypothesis or undischarged assumptions.

;Universal Instantiation (or Universal Elimination):
: formula_77
: formula_78

Restriction: No free occurrence of formula_71 in formula_2 falls within the scope of a quantifier quantifying a variable occurring in formula_69.

;Existential Generalization (or Existential Introduction):
: formula_82
: formula_83

Restriction: No free occurrence of formula_71 in formula_2 falls within the scope of a quantifier quantifying a variable occurring in formula_69.
;Existential Instantiation (or Existential Elimination):
